org.apache.archiva.event

Class Event

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.EventObject
      • org.apache.archiva.event.Event
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RepositoryEvent, RepositoryRegistryEvent

    public class Event
extends EventObject
implements Cloneable
    Base class for events. Events have a type and a source. The source is the instance that raised the event. There are different event types for a given event. The types are represented in a hierarchical structure. Events can be chained, which means a event listener can catch events and rethrow them as its own event.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
